---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Gary Wilson and The Unpackaged Traveler.">
  <section class="page-hero compact">
    <p class="tag">About</p>
    <h1>The playbook, not the package.</h1>
    <p>
      The Unpackaged Traveler is Gary Wilson's practical field guide to independent travel: 25 years of learning how to travel well for less, across 154 countries.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section about-intro">
    <div class="about-intro-copy">
      <p class="tag">The people behind it</p>
      <h2>Travel that stays with you.</h2>
      <p>
        I have spent much of my life looking for the kind of trip that is still memorable years later: places with strong local character, dramatic landscapes, history, good food, and a little discovery left in them. That has taken me across Africa, Asia, Latin America, Europe, Oceania, and the Middle East.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am drawn as much to mountains, deserts, islands, historic cities, and lesser-visited countries as I am to the practical question underneath every good trip: how do you make it work well, without paying somebody else to package every decision for you?
      </p>
      <dl class="facts-row">
        <div>
          <dt>On the road</dt>
          <dd>154 countries</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Learning the craft</dt>
          <dd>25 years</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Travel style</dt>
          <dd>Independent</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
    <figure class="about-photo about-photo-main">
      <img src="/images/about/gary-isabel-trek.png" alt="Gary and Isabel Wilson on a mountain trek" width="1061" height="1483" />
      <figcaption>Gary and Isabel, still choosing the long way round.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="section split-copy">
    <div>
      <p class="tag">Why this site exists</p>
      <h2>Adventure is not just for tour groups.</h2>
      <p>
        Many active US retirees still want movement, texture, and genuine discovery. What they do not need is a rushed itinerary, a coach window, or the feeling that an organised tour is their only realistic option.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site turns the research and hard-won lessons into clear, self-guided trip plans. The aim is simple: help you stay longer, travel bolder, spend less, and make decisions with confidence.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="note-panel">
      <h2>What you will find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Realistic day-by-day pacing, not an impossible highlight reel</li>
        <li>Transfer, hotel, cash, border, and booking details that affect the trip</li>
        <li>Clear costs and honest trade-offs, including where independent travel saves money</li>
        <li>Guides that say who a route suits, and who should choose something easier</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section split-copy">
    <div>
      <p class="tag">The standard</p>
      <h2>Useful beats glossy.</h2>
      <p>
        A beautiful destination is only half the story. The other half is whether the plan holds up in real life: the right amount of time, a workable connection, a sensible hotel, the cost of a missed detail, and enough room to enjoy the place rather than race through it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every plan is built to answer those questions plainly. It is not a substitute for checking current entry rules, health guidance, and local conditions before you book, but it should give you a far better starting point than a sales page or a generic listicle.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-aside-stack">
      <figure class="about-photo about-photo-compact">
        <img src="/images/about/couple-walking.png" alt="Gary and Isabel Wilson walking through an old town" width="294" height="294" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Walking through the places that make the planning worthwhile.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <aside class="note-panel">
        <h2>The promise</h2>
        <p>
          I will tell you what I would do, what I would skip, and where the friction is likely to be. No fantasy budgets. No pretending every transfer is effortless. No tour required.
        </p>
        <a class="text-link" href="/trip-plans/">Browse the trip plans</a>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section newsletter-band">
    <div>
      <p class="tag">Keep travelling</p>
      <h2>One full trip plan a month, lighter notes between.</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="muted">Get practical route ideas and planning notes for independent travel after the working years.</p>
      <a class="button primary" href="/subscribe/">Subscribe free <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
